review_blob: Ive drank this beer twice now. The first time I couldnt rate it because it was so absolutely wonderful that I was distracted. It has the perfect blend of bourbon, vanilla, and malty nose. Its smooth almost to its fault, as I can drink it as though its simply dessert(to be quickly devoured and absolutely enjoyed). I could and would drink a 6 pack of this for a hefty price. My deScription might not be concise or helpful but know this...if this beer hits your lips and you dont enjoy it, something is wrong with you.

First of all I am visiting my hometown(near Chicago) and my friend specifically tapped this when I didnt find anything on the tap list to wow me. The color is lighter than I normally enjoy.  It definitely tastes a little hoppier than previous firestones but I find it balances the slightly syrupy vanilla brown sugar flavors.  I taste a lot of parabola which Ill never complain about considering its in my top 5 favorite beers. Overall I am very excited about drinking many more of these.

Fell in love when I watched it pour. Super dark with a lovely creamy head.  Surprisingly lighter tasting than its appearance. Chocolatey and malty.  Overall very smooth, not overwhelming and I enjoyed it.

First off, its way to chilled. Even so Im enjoying the chocolate and mild coffee flavors. I believe or assume if this beer was warmer I would enjoy it tremendously. Too cold to figure it out completely.

I initially chose this beer by the fact it said it was brewed with bacon. So far Ive found it to be a brown ale that tastes more like a Belgian beer. As Im not a fan of Belgian beers as well as beers that claim to be brewed with bacon, but have zero greasy pork flavor.. I am not a fan. I find it thin and as my boyfriend would say it is laden with Belgian yeast.. I prefer my own yeast.

Im completely confused by this beer. Dark rich color but with no head.  Smells nothing like a stout. Tastes nothing like a stout. Seems grassy but not in a hoppy way, more in a dirty playground way. Im at a loss for words. Perhaps its because Im drinking in Oakland. Either way, pass this up.

Nice dark rich color. Has a fairly potent alcohol nose mixed with chocolate and malt. After 4th sip Im starting to find some hoppiness.. it seems contradictory.  Id rather it remain how it did my first sip.
